.TH "devm_acpi_dma_controller_register" 9 "devm_acpi_dma_controller_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_acpi_dma_controller_register \- resource managed acpi_dma_controller_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_acpi_dma_controller_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct dma_chan *(*acpi_dma_xlate) (struct acpi_dma_spec *, struct acpi_dma *) "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is registering this DMA controller
.IP "acpi_dma_xlate" 12
translation function
.IP "data" 12
pointer to controller specific data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBacpi_dma_controller_register\fP. DMA controller registered by this
function are automatically freed on driver detach. See
\fBacpi_dma_controller_register\fP for more information.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or appropriate errno value on error.
